DISASTER RECOVERY PLAN
================================================================================
Company: Ahmnest SecureTech Solution
Effective Date: [Date]
Version: 1.0
================================================================================

1. PURPOSE
================================================================================
This Disaster Recovery Plan outlines the procedures for restoring critical
IT systems and data following a disaster or significant disruption.

2. CRITICAL SYSTEMS
================================================================================
| System | Priority | RTO | RPO | Owner |
|--------|----------|-----|-----|-------|
| Email/Office 365 | 1 | 1 hour | 5 min | IT |
| Customer Database | 1 | 2 hours | 15 min | CTO |
| Website/Apps | 2 | 4 hours | 1 hour | IT |
| File Servers | 2 | 4 hours | 1 hour | IT |
| Financial Systems | 3 | 8 hours | 2 hours | CFO |
| HR Systems | 4 | 24 hours | 4 hours | HR |

3. DISASTER SCENARIOS
================================================================================
| Scenario | Impact | Recovery Strategy | Owner |
|----------|--------|-------------------|-------|
| Cyber Attack (Ransomware) | Data loss, system compromise | Restore from backups | IT/CTO |
| Natural Disaster (Fire/Flood) | Site inaccessible | Cloud failover | IT/CEO |
| Power Outage | System downtime | UPS + Generator | Facilities |
| Hardware Failure | System unavailable | Spare hardware | IT |
| Cloud Provider Outage | Service unavailable | Alternate provider | CTO |
| Human Error | Data loss/corruption | Restore from backups | IT |

4. RECOVERY STRATEGIES
================================================================================
| Strategy | Approach | Implementation |
|----------|----------|----------------|
| Hot Site | Fully operational alternate site | Cloud failover |
| Warm Site | Partially prepared site | Backup servers on AWS |
| Cold Site | Standby facility | Contract with provider |

5. RECOVERY PROCEDURES
================================================================================
5.1 Cyber Incident (Ransomware):
1. Activate incident response team
2. Isolate affected systems
3. Assess data corruption
4. Restore from clean backups (pre-incident)
5. Verify system integrity
6. Resume operations

5.2 Hardware Failure:
1. Identify failed components
2. Deploy backup hardware
3. Restore from backup
4. Verify functionality
5. Resume operations

6. TESTING SCHEDULE
================================================================================
| Test Type | Frequency | Participants | Success Criteria |
|-----------|-----------|--------------|------------------|
| Tabletop Exercise | Quarterly | Key stakeholders | Action plans updated |
| Full DR Test | Annually | All teams | RTO/RPO met |
| Partial Test | Semi-Annually | IT Team | Key systems recovered |

7. ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES
================================================================================
| Role | Responsibility | Backup/Alternate |
|------|----------------|------------------|
| CTO | Overall DR coordination | IT Manager |
| IT Lead | Technical recovery | Senior Admin |
| Operations | Facilities/Logistics | Office Manager |
| HR | Employee communication | HR Director |
| Communications | Client/Stakeholder comms | CEO |

